  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attack began with the attacker (0xd368cca925bb3dbadd06ea1b81e96a2174830978) executing a price-manipulation exploit via transaction 0xf5e753d3da60db214f2261343c1e1bc46e674d2fa4b7a953eaf3c52123aeebd2 on the Arbitrum network. Based on the attack signature and addresses involved, including interaction with Uniswap V3 Router (0xE592427A0AEce92De3Edee1F18E0157C05861564) and USDT (0xfd086bc7cd5c481dcc9c85ebe478a1c0b69fcbb9), the attacker likely utilized flash loans to manipulate asset prices before borrowing against inflated collateral values. The initial attack vector extracted approximately $60,000 across ETH, USDT, and ARB tokens, with total protocol losses estimated at $86,000. A proof-of-concept has been published by DeFiHackLabs, confirming the technical mechanics of the exploit.",
    "steps": [
      {
        "title": "Step 1",
        "detail": "Attacker address 0xd368cca925bb3dbadd06ea1b81e96a2174830978 accumulates approximately $60K in initial capital consisting of ETH, USDT, and ARB tokens on Arbitrum.",
